                <div class="section-break"></div>

                <p><strong>2. Personal Data We Collect</strong></p>
                
                <p><strong>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</strong></p>
                <p>When you submit your application or CV through our website, we collect:</p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Identity Data:</strong> Full name, title, date of birth (if included in CV)</li>
                    <li><strong>Contact Data:</strong> Email address, telephone numbers, postal address</li>
                    <li><strong>Professional Data:</strong> Employment history, educational qualifications, professional certifications, skills, languages</li>
                    <li><strong>Application Data:</strong> CV/resume, cover letter, portfolio links, references</li>
                    <li><strong>Preference Data:</strong> Job preferences, desired salary range, location preferences, availability</li>
                    <li><strong>Communication Data:</strong> Records of our correspondence and interactions</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</strong></p>
                <p>When you visit our website, we automatically collect:</p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, time zone setting, browser plug-in types</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you use our website, including pages visited and links clicked</li>
                    <li><strong>Form Submission Data:</strong> Timestamp of when you submitted your application</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>2.3 Information from Third Parties</strong></p>
                <p>We may receive information about you from:</p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Public Sources:</strong> LinkedIn profiles, professional websites, public directories</li>
                    <li><strong>Referrals:</strong> Information provided by colleagues or other professionals who recommend you</li>
                    <li><strong>Background Check Providers:</strong> Only with your explicit consent and where legally required</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="section-break"></div>

                <p><strong>3. How We Use Your Personal Data</strong></p>
                <p>We only use your personal data where we have a lawful basis. Here's specifically how and why we process your information:</p>
                
                <p><strong>3.1 For Job Seekers/Candidates</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Process your application for specific vacancies</strong> - All categories listed in Section 2 - Legitimate interest (matching candidates to roles)</li>
                    <li><strong>Assess your suitability for current and future positions</strong> - Professional and application data - Legitimate interest</li>
                    <li><strong>Communicate with you about job opportunities</strong> - Contact data - Legitimate interest for initial contact; consent for ongoing communications</li>
                    <li><strong>Maintain our talent pool for future opportunities</strong> - All categories - Consent (you must opt-in)</li>
                    <li><strong>Conduct reference and background checks</strong> - Identity and professional data - Legitimate interest or legal obligation</li>
                    <li><strong>Comply with legal obligations</strong> - All categories as required - Legal obligation</li>
                    <li><strong>Defend against legal claims</strong> - All categories as necessary - Legitimate interest</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="section-break"></div>

                <p><strong>4. Who We Share Your Data With</strong></p>
                <p>We share your personal data only when necessary and with appropriate safeguards:</p>
                
                <p><strong>4.1 Categories of Recipients</strong></p>
                <p><strong>Service Providers (Data Processors):</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Netlify Inc.</strong> (USA) - Website hosting and form processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Google Ireland Limited</strong> - Document storage (Google Drive)</li>
                    <li><strong>Notion Labs Inc.</strong> (USA) - Internal documentation and candidate tracking</li>
                    <li><strong>Calendly LLC</strong> (USA) - Interview scheduling</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Business Partners:</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Client Companies:</strong> We share candidate profiles with prospective employers only after informing you and confirming your interest in the specific opportunity</li>
                    <li><strong>Partner Recruitment Firms:</strong> Located in EU countries and Brazil, operating under strict confidentiality agreements</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="section-break"></div>

                <p><strong>5. Data Retention</strong></p>
                <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes described:</p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Unsuccessful applications:</strong> 6 months from final decision</li>
                    <li><strong>Talent pool profiles:</strong> 24 months from last update (with consent)</li>
                    <li><strong>Successful placements:</strong> Duration of employment + 6 years</li>
                    <li><strong>Client records:</strong> 6 years from last interaction</li>
                    <li><strong>Email correspondence:</strong> 3 years</li>
                    <li><strong>Website usage data:</strong> 12 months</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="section-break"></div>

                <p><strong>6. Your Rights</strong></p>
                <p>Under GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
                <ul class="list-bulleted">
                    <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data we hold</li>
                    <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
                    <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data (in certain circumstances)</li>
                    <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Limit how we use your data</li>
                    <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
                    <li><strong>Object:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
                    <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Where we rely on consent, withdraw it at any time</li>
                    <li><strong>Complain:</strong> Lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority</li>
                </ul>
                <p>To exercise any right, email vincent@luxsearch.eu. We'll respond within 30 days and never charge a fee unless requests are manifestly unfounded or excessive.</p>

